WEBVTT

00:07.667 --> 00:10.792
(wind blowing)

00:17.083 --> 00:20.000
(squeaking)

00:20.083 --> 00:23.166
(power lines buzzing)

00:23.250 --> 00:26.375
(rattling)

00:27.625 --> 00:30.625
(serene music playing)

00:30.709 --> 00:33.917
(wind gently blowing)

00:35.000 --> 00:37.083
♪

00:50.458 --> 00:53.625
(birds chirping)

01:08.959 --> 01:11.125
(power lines buzzing)

01:14.291 --> 01:16.375
♪ ♪

01:25.333 --> 01:28.709
Talulah:
(sighs) God, it's freezing here.

01:28.792 --> 01:30.792
Ellie:
It's freezing at
home as well, Lu.

01:30.875 --> 01:33.291
Talulah:
Yeah, but we're here.

01:33.375 --> 01:35.917
-I mean, why?
-I told you, baby.

01:36.000 --> 01:38.750
It's Ellie's birthday surprise.

01:38.834 --> 01:42.250
It'll be great.
Do you know this place
is full of archaeology?

01:42.333 --> 01:45.000
I read there were
Saxons there and Celts.

01:45.083 --> 01:46.542
Even Vikings, Lu!

01:46.625 --> 01:48.458
God, that sounds boring.

01:48.542 --> 01:51.542
And the cottage I've got
us to stay is lovely.

01:51.625 --> 01:53.166
It's really lovely.

01:53.250 --> 01:55.333
Talulah:
(sighs) Archaeology's
just dead things.

01:55.417 --> 01:57.667
-Shut up, you.
-You shut up.

01:57.750 --> 02:01.041
Stop it!
Let's not argue, okay?

02:01.125 --> 02:03.250
This is our little holiday,
just for us three,

02:03.333 --> 02:05.959
so no fighting, alright?

02:06.041 --> 02:07.500
Sorry, Mom.

02:08.750 --> 02:10.417
Talulah:
You didn't even ask.

02:10.500 --> 02:12.792
And I was getting
ready for school.

02:12.875 --> 02:15.417
Helen:
Yeah, well, that's what
a surprise is, Lu.

02:15.500 --> 02:17.667
Yeah. That's the reason.

02:17.750 --> 02:19.917
Not 'cause Ellie went
all psycho in class.

02:20.000 --> 02:22.750
Helen:
Hey! You've made
your point, Talulah.

02:22.834 --> 02:24.959
You've made it for
the last 50 miles, alright?

02:25.041 --> 02:26.834
And can you put that away,
please?

02:26.917 --> 02:30.333
We're not spending
our entire holiday
looking at screens.

02:30.875 --> 02:32.041
Jeez.

02:33.875 --> 02:35.041
Talulah:
Anyway,

02:35.125 --> 02:37.959
I thought we couldn't
afford to go away.

02:39.834 --> 02:41.208
No.

02:42.417 --> 02:44.583
No, I mean...

02:44.667 --> 02:47.291
Things have been tight,
but we're not broke.

02:47.375 --> 02:49.834
(quietly):
That's not what Gran said.

02:49.917 --> 02:51.583
Helen:
What did Gran say?

02:53.083 --> 02:54.250
Lu?

02:54.792 --> 02:57.166
What did Gran say?

02:57.250 --> 03:00.625
She said you couldn't make
the mortgage this month.

03:02.750 --> 03:04.083
Well, don't listen to your Gran

03:04.166 --> 03:06.125
'cause your Gran
is bloody mental.

03:06.208 --> 03:09.166
(giggling)

03:09.250 --> 03:12.375
♪ ♪

03:19.125 --> 03:22.291
(birds chirping)

03:25.208 --> 03:27.583
Your go, Lu. "L."

03:27.667 --> 03:29.500
Easy. Lamb.

03:29.583 --> 03:31.875
-Helen: Ah.
-Lamb's not an animal.

03:31.959 --> 03:33.125
Then what is it?

03:34.208 --> 03:35.542
It's a baby sheep.

03:35.625 --> 03:37.458
And that's an animal.

03:37.542 --> 03:38.959
-She can't have "lamb."
-Talulah: Twenty points.

03:39.041 --> 03:40.458
Helen:
Let her have "lamb," Ellie.

03:40.542 --> 03:42.667
-I couldn't have "kitten."
-Helen: Come on!

03:42.750 --> 03:44.500
You let her get
away with everything.

03:44.583 --> 03:47.000
Helen:
Let her have "lamb."

03:58.959 --> 04:02.125
(birds chirping)

04:03.166 --> 04:05.333
Helen:
Oh my God! (laughs)

04:06.709 --> 04:08.834
Wow!

04:09.458 --> 04:11.417
Well, here we are!

04:11.500 --> 04:12.875
(car stops)

04:15.250 --> 04:17.417
Talulah:
A-are we driving on that?

04:17.500 --> 04:19.458
Yeah! It's a causeway!

04:19.542 --> 04:21.291
It was built by the Romans.

04:21.375 --> 04:23.959
-It's gonna be great.
-That was a long time ago.

04:24.625 --> 04:27.208
It's perfectly safe.

04:27.291 --> 04:29.667
We're going to that island
over there. Can you see it?

04:29.750 --> 04:31.250
It's called Osea.

04:31.333 --> 04:33.000
Isn't it incredible?

04:33.083 --> 04:35.834
We're gonna have so much
fun, aren't we? Yeah?

04:36.834 --> 04:39.000
-(Talulah sighs)
-Helen: Huh?

04:39.750 --> 04:41.500
Okay, here we go.

04:43.041 --> 04:45.959
♪ ♪

04:46.041 --> 04:48.208
(birds chirping)

05:01.208 --> 05:03.583
Ellie:
What happens when
the tide comes in?

05:03.667 --> 05:05.542
Helen:
Well, then the road's closed.

05:05.625 --> 05:07.291
Talulah:
What, you mean we're stuck?

05:07.375 --> 05:09.458
(light strings playing)

05:09.542 --> 05:11.709
♪

05:15.291 --> 05:17.375
God, it's like
driving on the sea!

05:17.458 --> 05:19.542
(chuckles)

05:22.208 --> 05:24.250
(car bouncing)

05:25.041 --> 05:27.000
It's really bumpy, Mom.

05:27.083 --> 05:29.667
No, it's fine, darling.
It's very safe.

05:29.750 --> 05:31.417
-(hard bounce)
-Ooh! Shit.

05:31.500 --> 05:33.917
Hey! That's a swear.
You've only got two left.

05:34.583 --> 05:36.500
(bouncing continues)

05:36.583 --> 05:39.709
This is mad, driving on this.

05:42.959 --> 05:46.083
♪ ♪

05:49.959 --> 05:52.083
(birds chirping)

06:11.166 --> 06:12.500
Mom?

06:14.166 --> 06:15.834
It's great,
isn't it?

06:17.333 --> 06:19.125
I mean, it's atmospheric.

06:20.625 --> 06:22.834
-It's creepy.
-Look, just...

06:22.917 --> 06:25.417
-I don't like it, Mom.
-Helen: Give it a chance, Lu.

06:25.500 --> 06:26.625
(sighs)

06:32.917 --> 06:34.291
(sighs)

06:42.875 --> 06:45.959
♪ ♪

07:12.667 --> 07:14.834
Talulah:
What a dump.

07:17.542 --> 07:20.041
♪ ♪

07:47.125 --> 07:50.208
♪ ♪

08:02.542 --> 08:05.625
-(indistinct chatter)
-(man sobbing)

08:05.709 --> 08:08.250
Talulah:
Is that man crying?

08:10.709 --> 08:12.417
Helen:
It's not far now.

08:22.583 --> 08:25.667
-(wind blowing)
-(birds chittering)

08:25.750 --> 08:27.625
Helen:
See?

08:27.709 --> 08:29.333
I think we're in that
cottage over there.

08:29.417 --> 08:31.041
Isn't it beautiful?

08:31.125 --> 08:32.500
Is there Wi-Fi?

08:32.583 --> 08:35.542
-(sighs)
-Ellie: Mom, what about Gran?

08:35.625 --> 08:38.166
She said she wanted to take
me to her Bible group tonight.

08:38.250 --> 08:41.375
Yeah. She called.
It was canceled
'cause of the weather.

08:41.458 --> 08:42.792
Really?

08:42.875 --> 08:45.125
No, Ellie, I'm lying to you.

08:45.208 --> 08:47.500
But don't you like all this?

08:47.583 --> 08:49.750
Oh no. Yeah, I do.

08:50.417 --> 08:52.208
-It's great, Mom.
-Great.

08:52.291 --> 08:53.542
You two stay here
where it's warm,

08:53.625 --> 08:55.709
and I'll go and sort
it all out, alright?

08:55.792 --> 08:57.875
(wind whistling)

08:57.959 --> 09:00.333
"Oh no.
Yeah, it's great, Mom."

09:01.792 --> 09:03.125
(sighs)

09:06.750 --> 09:08.542
(knocking)

09:08.625 --> 09:11.041
-(leaves rustling)
-(cows lowing)

09:11.125 --> 09:12.792
(knocking)

09:18.417 --> 09:21.792
-(wind blowing)
-(lowing continues)

09:26.250 --> 09:29.250
(tense music playing)

09:29.333 --> 09:31.792
♪

09:44.625 --> 09:47.417
-Man: Can I help you?
-Jesus Christ!

09:47.500 --> 09:50.417
(laughing)
Shit! Oh my God!

09:50.500 --> 09:53.000
Sorry!
You really scared me. Um,

09:53.083 --> 09:56.417
sorry. Are you Alan?

09:56.500 --> 10:00.083
I'm Helen. I'm booked
to stay here today.

10:00.166 --> 10:02.417
-Today?
-Yeah.

10:02.500 --> 10:04.834
-This is the cottage, right?
-No.

10:04.917 --> 10:07.834
I mean yes, yes, it is.
It's just...

10:07.917 --> 10:09.750
Look, you can't. Not today.

10:09.834 --> 10:11.250
What?

10:11.333 --> 10:12.917
No, I-I, um...

10:13.000 --> 10:14.750
I booked it online
just this morning.

10:14.834 --> 10:16.458
I've got the Airbnb
thing here--

10:16.542 --> 10:19.125
I'm afraid it's not possible.

10:19.208 --> 10:21.250
What do you mean
not possible?

10:21.333 --> 10:23.709
I've driven from London.
I've got my kids in the car.

10:23.792 --> 10:25.792
I've paid to stay
in this cottage.

10:25.875 --> 10:27.959
Look, I-I don't
want any trouble.

10:28.041 --> 10:30.959
-I beg your pardon?
-Just leave, please.

10:31.041 --> 10:33.291
We'll refund you
the money.

10:33.375 --> 10:35.792
It's not about
the fucking money!

10:35.875 --> 10:37.000
I'm gonna report you.

10:37.083 --> 10:39.792
If you don't let us in
this cottage right now,

10:39.875 --> 10:41.625
I'm reporting you, okay?

10:41.709 --> 10:43.333
Alright.

10:43.417 --> 10:44.792
I really am very sorry.

10:44.875 --> 10:47.458
-(wind blowing)
-(cows lowing)

10:47.542 --> 10:49.166
Helen:
Hey!

10:51.208 --> 10:53.333
Oh no, no.
You can't come in.

10:53.417 --> 10:55.709
Look, I-I booked to
stay in this cottage.

10:55.792 --> 10:57.750
No, that shouldn't
have happened.

10:57.834 --> 11:01.000
We don't do
holiday lets no more.
We're done with that.

11:01.083 --> 11:04.333
-He should've taken
it down off that thing.
-Yeah, well, he didn't!

11:04.417 --> 11:06.333
And I've driven all
morning to get here,

11:06.417 --> 11:08.125
and I've got two
kids in that car

11:08.208 --> 11:10.709
who are cold
and hungry and tired!

11:12.125 --> 11:15.041
Their dad was
white then, was he?

11:15.125 --> 11:18.667
-Are you serious?
-Woman: The causeway
closes in two hours.

11:18.750 --> 11:19.583
Go home.

11:19.667 --> 11:21.875
Believe me,
it's for the best.

11:21.959 --> 11:23.750
Tell me something.

11:23.834 --> 11:27.000
When did you decide your
cottage wasn't available?

11:27.083 --> 11:29.625
-Was it when you saw me?
-No! No!

11:29.709 --> 11:32.500
It's nothing like that,
I swear. It's just...

11:32.583 --> 11:35.000
Look, there's lots of lovely
places on the mainland--

11:35.083 --> 11:38.333
Oh, fuck the mainland,
and fuck you!

11:38.417 --> 11:40.667
I'm reporting you,
do you understand?

11:40.750 --> 11:44.083
And believe me,
we are staying
on this island tonight.

11:45.208 --> 11:46.417
(car door opens)

11:48.375 --> 11:50.041
-What was all that about?
-(door shuts)

11:50.125 --> 11:52.458
It was just a mix-up with
the booking, that's all.

11:52.542 --> 11:54.542
They didn't look nice, Mom.

11:54.625 --> 11:56.750
They were fine, hon.
They were lovely.

11:56.834 --> 12:00.000
Just a--
Just a mix-up, that's all.

12:00.083 --> 12:02.458
(sighs) But look!

12:02.542 --> 12:05.417
Let's find somewhere
else, yeah?

12:05.500 --> 12:08.458
(birds chirping)

12:08.542 --> 12:11.667
(wind blowing)

12:17.291 --> 12:20.083
What about, uh,
the hotel back there?

12:20.166 --> 12:22.875
Talulah:
It looked shut. And creepy.

12:23.750 --> 12:26.041
And doesn't that
sea road close soon?

12:26.125 --> 12:29.333
No. We've still
got two hours, yeah?

12:30.750 --> 12:33.583
But, what if we
don't find anywhere?

12:33.667 --> 12:37.000
Helen:
Course we will.
This is England.

12:37.667 --> 12:38.750
How about this?

12:38.834 --> 12:41.417
We are gonna have ourselves
an adventure, right?

12:41.500 --> 12:42.750
Just us three.

12:42.834 --> 12:45.166
We're gonna find somewhere
really, really brilliant

12:45.250 --> 12:47.667
-to stay on this island
within the next two hours--
-Talulah: Mom?

12:47.750 --> 12:50.750
Hold on. Within
the next two hours,

12:50.834 --> 12:52.917
and if we don't find anywhere,

12:53.000 --> 12:55.166
then we'll go home.

12:56.417 --> 12:57.667
What do you say?

12:57.750 --> 12:59.583
(sighs)

12:59.667 --> 13:01.792
I need a wee.

13:07.542 --> 13:09.709
(doors shut)

13:09.792 --> 13:11.917
(birds chirping)

13:20.542 --> 13:23.250
Talulah:
It's too cold! I can't wee!

13:29.625 --> 13:32.834
(wind blowing, trees creaking)

13:51.625 --> 13:53.875
I would've been
okay today, Mom.

13:57.083 --> 13:58.625
What I'm saying is...

13:58.709 --> 14:01.083
you don't have to
worry about me...

14:01.166 --> 14:02.417
at school.

14:02.500 --> 14:04.333
Els!

14:04.417 --> 14:06.375
This is your birthday surprise!

14:06.458 --> 14:08.375
I planned it ages ago.

14:08.458 --> 14:11.250
It's got nothing to do
with those stupid girls.

14:12.792 --> 14:14.125
Look.

14:15.583 --> 14:17.250
This year...

14:17.333 --> 14:20.166
It's been really hard
on all three of us.

14:20.250 --> 14:22.875
This holiday is
like a new start.

14:22.959 --> 14:25.583
Just you, me, and Lu.

14:25.667 --> 14:28.875
I want it to be special.
Will you help me?

14:28.959 --> 14:30.500
Well,
I went for a wee,

14:30.583 --> 14:33.291
but I think I might
need a poo now.

14:35.000 --> 14:37.875
But, it can wait.

14:37.959 --> 14:41.250
-(animal screeching)
-(birds flapping)

14:44.333 --> 14:45.792
What was that?

14:47.750 --> 14:50.250
Sounded like a cow.

14:50.333 --> 14:52.500
Do they kill cows here?

14:52.583 --> 14:54.583
Well, they...
they have farms.

14:54.667 --> 14:58.542
And how do you think you get
your burgers? Get in the car.

14:58.625 --> 15:00.208
Ellie:
Makes me wanna go vegetarian.

15:00.291 --> 15:01.917
Talulah:
Makes me want a burger.

15:05.458 --> 15:08.625
(birds chirping)

15:13.375 --> 15:15.500
(dog barking)

15:17.959 --> 15:21.083
Helen:
Okay! You both stay here.

15:21.166 --> 15:23.458
And no screens, okay?

15:23.959 --> 15:25.291
Thank you.

15:26.959 --> 15:28.166
(door shuts)

15:28.250 --> 15:31.375
(dog barking)

15:33.500 --> 15:34.917
(tablet beeping)

15:35.000 --> 15:37.166
(barking continues)

15:43.834 --> 15:46.208
(metal creaking)

15:56.542 --> 15:59.667
(clock ticking)

16:08.709 --> 16:11.333
(indistinct chatter)

16:11.417 --> 16:14.834
-Man 1: Me? What are
you talking about?
-Man 2: It's just in case.

16:16.792 --> 16:18.667
Man 1:
I don't know if
I think like that.

16:18.750 --> 16:20.458
Man 2:
I thought you knew
what you were doing.

16:20.542 --> 16:23.125
Man 1:
Yeah, but not about
things like that.

16:23.208 --> 16:24.959
What if it goes wrong?

16:25.041 --> 16:27.041
I'm scared.

16:27.125 --> 16:30.000
I don't wanna hurt anyone.

16:30.083 --> 16:33.166
It's not others getting hurt
you should worry about.

16:33.250 --> 16:34.625
Man 3:
There's no need for that.

16:34.709 --> 16:36.709
Man 2:
There's no one
fucking talking to you.

16:36.792 --> 16:39.917
♪ ♪

16:41.583 --> 16:43.750
Sorry.
I was just, um...

16:47.417 --> 16:50.500
You are doing this.
You are.

16:50.583 --> 16:53.750
♪ ♪

17:06.375 --> 17:09.125
I-I was, um... (sighs)

17:09.208 --> 17:11.417
Sorry. I didn't mean to...

17:13.583 --> 17:16.291
-Are you alright?
-Just a...

17:16.375 --> 17:18.500
misunderstanding.

17:19.875 --> 17:21.959
The boy...

17:23.166 --> 17:25.792
is a tad abrasive.

17:26.917 --> 17:28.667
But he means well.

17:31.875 --> 17:32.875
Um...

17:32.959 --> 17:34.875
I'm Janny.

17:34.959 --> 17:37.625
(uncorks bottle, pouring)

17:37.709 --> 17:40.417
I own this place.

17:46.000 --> 17:47.125
(sighs)

17:47.208 --> 17:50.583
I'm afraid you've caught us
at a moment of incapacity.

17:50.667 --> 17:51.875
We're closed.

17:51.959 --> 17:54.750
-(pouring)
-Right, okay, and,
um, when do you open?

17:54.834 --> 17:56.250
No.

17:56.333 --> 17:58.667
I mean, we're closed down.

18:00.500 --> 18:03.041
-It's just I-I need a room.
-(pouring)

18:03.125 --> 18:05.583
Is there anywhere
else that has rooms?

18:05.667 --> 18:08.000
(sighs) No.

18:08.542 --> 18:10.667
Not anymore.

18:13.083 --> 18:15.834
-(sighs)
-What happened to your head?

18:19.250 --> 18:20.583
A knock.

18:20.667 --> 18:23.917
I was getting something
from the kitchen cupboard
and it fell out,

18:24.000 --> 18:25.667
clumped me.

18:27.166 --> 18:28.875
Silly really.

18:29.583 --> 18:31.333
Lemme look at it for you.

18:32.667 --> 18:35.333
(footsteps approaching)

18:43.375 --> 18:44.542
(object clatters)

18:46.709 --> 18:51.166
-(undoes seatbelt)
-Talulah: Hey! Mom said
to stay in the car!

18:56.750 --> 18:59.875
♪ ♪

19:01.834 --> 19:04.417
Hey! Hey!

19:06.083 --> 19:07.291
Um, you dropped something.

19:07.375 --> 19:09.667
What are you doing?

19:09.750 --> 19:13.041
She... she dropped
this, and I...

19:13.125 --> 19:14.709
Not you.

19:19.083 --> 19:22.500
-(metal clinks)
-You think this is
a day for messing?

19:22.583 --> 19:25.417
You're needed, fast.

19:26.750 --> 19:28.375
Go on.

19:30.333 --> 19:32.583
♪ ♪

19:40.125 --> 19:42.333
And who are you?

19:42.417 --> 19:44.583
Um, I'm Ellie.

19:45.166 --> 19:46.917
I'm here with my mom.

19:48.125 --> 19:50.250
And why are you here, Ellie?

19:50.333 --> 19:52.542
A birthday surprise.

19:52.625 --> 19:54.750
For me. Um...

19:54.834 --> 19:57.125
It's my birthday
in two days.

19:57.208 --> 19:58.667
Okay.

19:58.750 --> 20:01.125
And how old will you be
in two days, Ellie?

20:01.208 --> 20:03.834
-14.
-14...

20:05.000 --> 20:07.125
That's a nice age.

20:08.458 --> 20:10.500
♪ ♪

20:10.583 --> 20:12.583
You know what that is?

20:12.667 --> 20:14.375
That's a Sheela na gig.

20:14.458 --> 20:17.458
You'll find them on churches
all over this country.

20:17.542 --> 20:19.291
They're odd little things.

20:19.375 --> 20:22.125
No one really knows
who put them there.

20:23.458 --> 20:26.291
What do you think?
You like that?

20:28.792 --> 20:30.375
Um, I should get back--

20:30.458 --> 20:33.041
But, why this place
for your birthday?

20:33.125 --> 20:35.709
My mom thinks
I like archaeology.

20:35.792 --> 20:37.500
And do you?

20:37.583 --> 20:39.041
You like archaeology?

20:39.125 --> 20:41.667
-No? (laughs) Moms, eh?
-(Ellie laughs)

20:43.583 --> 20:44.792
Look.

20:44.875 --> 20:48.166
You ever seen anything
like this before?

20:50.375 --> 20:52.625
What-- what is that?

20:52.709 --> 20:55.583
Oh, I thought you didn't
like archaeology.

20:55.667 --> 20:58.333
Well,
I sort of like it a bit.

20:59.542 --> 21:02.000
This is Saxon.

21:02.083 --> 21:04.792
♪ ♪

21:04.875 --> 21:07.083
It's over 1,000 years old.

21:07.166 --> 21:10.125
It's worth more than
everything on this island.

21:10.208 --> 21:13.083
It's from the Battle of Maldon,
fought right here on Osea.

21:13.166 --> 21:15.417
-Really?
-Really.

21:15.500 --> 21:17.542
The Saxon Lord Byrhtnoth invited

21:17.625 --> 21:20.291
4,000 Vikings to come over

21:20.375 --> 21:22.208
and slaughter him
and all his men.

21:22.291 --> 21:24.000
Invited them.

21:24.500 --> 21:26.667
Total massacre.

21:27.291 --> 21:28.667
Y-you know why he asked them

21:28.750 --> 21:32.041
to come over and butcher him
and all his men?

21:33.542 --> 21:35.041
Because it was meant.

21:35.125 --> 21:38.000
And what's meant to happen
always happens on Osea,

21:38.083 --> 21:39.709
no matter what.

21:42.625 --> 21:43.875
Would you like to hold it?

21:43.959 --> 21:47.750
♪ ♪

21:54.208 --> 21:56.375
This is quite a nasty knock.

21:57.375 --> 21:59.458
Are you a doctor?

21:59.542 --> 22:00.583
No.

22:01.417 --> 22:03.458
But I used to be a vet.

22:03.542 --> 22:06.792
Mammalian flesh is
mammalian flesh, hm?

22:08.250 --> 22:10.083
Such...

22:10.166 --> 22:12.792
very kind hands.

22:13.625 --> 22:15.959
Makes me wish
I were a Cockapoo.

22:16.041 --> 22:18.125
(laughs)

22:20.333 --> 22:22.125
(sips, sighs)

22:23.208 --> 22:26.000
And what brings you
and your...

22:26.083 --> 22:29.291
insanely tender
hands to Osea?

22:31.500 --> 22:33.166
My, um...

22:33.250 --> 22:36.208
-my daughter.
She loves archaeology.
-Ah.

22:38.083 --> 22:40.041
We had a place to stay.

22:40.125 --> 22:42.000
It was a lovely place.

22:42.083 --> 22:44.208
Airbnb, but, um,

22:44.291 --> 22:47.458
when we got here,
it suddenly became unavailable.

22:47.542 --> 22:50.125
Almost like they didn't like
the look of me or something.

22:51.792 --> 22:53.750
Oh no. No, dear.

22:53.834 --> 22:55.792
No, the people here,
they're guilty of many sins,

22:55.875 --> 22:58.000
but that's not one of them.

22:58.750 --> 23:00.875
It's just been a...

23:00.959 --> 23:02.625
tricky day.

23:03.667 --> 23:05.000
Look.

23:05.083 --> 23:08.000
I really need
somewhere to stay.

23:08.083 --> 23:09.667
My girls have
been through a lot.

23:09.750 --> 23:13.792
This has been, like,
a really tough year.

23:13.875 --> 23:17.125
And we're on this break
and I can't afford it.

23:18.166 --> 23:20.208
I really can't.

23:20.291 --> 23:22.500
And I just need it
to be special.

23:23.709 --> 23:25.291
I'm sorry.

23:25.375 --> 23:26.667
I can't.

23:27.625 --> 23:29.333
I just can't.

23:30.667 --> 23:32.000
Why?

23:32.083 --> 23:34.583
Why is it so important to you?

23:34.667 --> 23:36.458
♪ ♪

23:36.542 --> 23:38.667
I want them to feel good.

23:39.333 --> 23:41.041
(chuckles)

23:41.125 --> 23:42.750
Then leave.

23:42.834 --> 23:46.000
(indistinct chatter)

23:48.792 --> 23:50.417
(door opens)

23:50.500 --> 23:53.709
Helen:
Hey! Hey! You!

23:53.792 --> 23:56.458
-What did you say to her?!
-Larry: Excuse me?
"What did I say to her?"

23:56.542 --> 23:58.250
No, Mom,
he was just--

23:58.333 --> 24:00.083
Why are you talking
to my daughter?!

24:00.166 --> 24:02.083
Ellie:
Mom, he was just
showing me something.

24:02.166 --> 24:04.208
I have told you
not to talk!

24:04.291 --> 24:07.166
-How many times have
I told you not to talk--
-Talk to what?

24:07.250 --> 24:09.333
Get in the car, now.

24:12.125 --> 24:15.291
She's 13, okay?

24:15.375 --> 24:18.333
-13!
-Why are you telling me that?

24:19.709 --> 24:21.125
Look, I-I'm not--
I'm just saying--

24:21.208 --> 24:23.959
Why the fuck are
you telling me that?
What do you think I am?

24:24.041 --> 24:25.792
Look, I'm not--
I'm not trying to offend--

24:25.875 --> 24:28.875
Well, it's a bit late
for that now, cunt.

24:30.709 --> 24:32.166
I'll call the police.

24:33.250 --> 24:35.291
Yeah?

24:35.375 --> 24:37.792
How long do you think it'll
take them to get here?

24:37.875 --> 24:39.375
Man:
Larry!

24:41.208 --> 24:43.250
She over-reacted,
that's all.

24:43.333 --> 24:44.834
She was scared for her daughter.

24:44.917 --> 24:47.792
(tense music playing)

24:47.875 --> 24:50.000
We don't need any
nonsense. Not today.

24:53.709 --> 24:55.917
Why the fuck are
you here, anyway?

24:57.083 --> 24:58.208
Hey?

25:05.542 --> 25:06.917
You okay?

25:12.333 --> 25:14.750
♪ ♪

25:17.500 --> 25:20.250
(tablet beeping)

25:24.250 --> 25:25.417
(door slams)

25:28.583 --> 25:30.208
What did I say
about screens?!

25:31.417 --> 25:33.917
No screens! What did
I say about screens?!

25:34.000 --> 25:36.792
Ellie:
Mom, Mom, it was okay--

25:36.875 --> 25:38.542
No, it wasn't!

25:38.625 --> 25:41.709
You don't know who he was!
You never know who anyone is!

25:41.792 --> 25:43.458
Everyone is a stranger!

25:43.542 --> 25:45.875
I have told you
hundreds of times!

25:45.959 --> 25:48.041
It could be anyone! Any man!

25:48.125 --> 25:50.041
Any man c--

25:50.125 --> 25:52.917
(hyperventilating)

25:53.000 --> 25:55.583
-What if I lost you?
What if I lost you, too?
-Mom.

25:55.667 --> 25:57.750
-What if I lost you?
-Mom. Mom!

25:57.834 --> 26:01.417
-(indistinct babbling)
-Ellie: We're here, okay?

26:01.500 --> 26:03.000
Me and Talulah.

26:03.083 --> 26:05.125
-(gasping)
-We're both here.

26:05.208 --> 26:07.875
♪ ♪

26:07.959 --> 26:09.750
We're here. We're all here.

26:09.834 --> 26:12.834
(Helen gasping)

26:16.500 --> 26:19.500
(waves washing ashore)

26:19.583 --> 26:22.000
(wind blowing)

26:23.542 --> 26:25.667
(bird chirping)

26:34.250 --> 26:37.375
(trees creaking)

26:41.959 --> 26:44.166
Talulah:
Do you think she's alright?

26:44.834 --> 26:46.834
Ellie:
I think so.

26:47.667 --> 26:49.542
She's just got this...

26:49.625 --> 26:51.917
birthday thing in her head.

26:52.000 --> 26:54.166
Like she has to
make it special.

26:55.333 --> 26:57.208
Do you really wanna
stay here though?

26:57.291 --> 26:59.500
I mean,
it feels just...

27:00.250 --> 27:01.875
sad.

27:05.417 --> 27:08.542
It'll be fine once she
finds us a place to stay.

27:08.625 --> 27:11.250
(phone vibrating)

27:11.333 --> 27:14.166
(opens, shuts glove compartment)

27:14.250 --> 27:15.834
It's Gran.

27:17.291 --> 27:18.959
Hi, Gran.

27:19.041 --> 27:21.417
(indistinct phone chatter)

27:22.792 --> 27:24.375
What?

27:25.000 --> 27:27.667
No. But it's canceled.

27:28.625 --> 27:31.250
(Gran continues, muffled)

27:34.542 --> 27:36.750
But Mom said...

27:36.834 --> 27:39.834
♪ ♪

27:39.917 --> 27:42.542
(bird cawing)

27:45.583 --> 27:48.542
(water flowing)

27:48.625 --> 27:50.250
(sighs)

27:55.667 --> 27:56.750
(sniffs)

27:59.083 --> 28:02.208
(shivering)

28:04.458 --> 28:07.917
(serene music playing)

28:08.000 --> 28:10.083
♪ ♪

28:12.917 --> 28:15.750
(bird squawking)

28:36.625 --> 28:39.750
♪ ♪

28:56.792 --> 28:58.959
(music intensifies)

29:15.000 --> 29:16.625
I think I found something.

29:16.709 --> 29:18.875
-And...
-Talulah: Let me see.

29:18.959 --> 29:21.250
-Wow.
-Talulah: I wanna see!
Let me see!

29:21.333 --> 29:23.417
-Ellie: Is that
here on the island?
-Yes.

29:23.500 --> 29:24.959
It's a new development
right here.

29:25.041 --> 29:27.208
-Look at those huts, Lu!
-Do you stay in those?

29:27.291 --> 29:31.125
Yeah! They got a mini spa
with a teensy tiny little pool.

29:31.208 --> 29:33.291
(gasp) Cute!

29:33.375 --> 29:35.375
It looks really good, Mom.

29:35.458 --> 29:37.166
I think we
should try it.

29:38.500 --> 29:40.625
Are the pools heated?

29:40.709 --> 29:43.125
I don't know.
We'll have to find out.

29:43.208 --> 29:45.125
-Can I play on
your phone, please?
-No. No.

29:45.208 --> 29:47.041
-Why?
-Because I need it!

29:47.125 --> 29:49.834
-(annoyed sigh)
-Alright, let's get going.

29:56.375 --> 29:59.500
(wind blowing)

30:03.333 --> 30:05.333
Okay. It's just up this road.

30:05.750 --> 30:07.083
Talulah:
Okay.

30:08.667 --> 30:09.875
What road?

30:09.959 --> 30:12.750
-Helen: We must've
come the wrong way.
-Ellie: No.

30:12.834 --> 30:15.041
This is what it says on Maps.

30:15.875 --> 30:18.500
(birds chirping)

30:25.875 --> 30:27.458
(sighs)

30:36.458 --> 30:37.792
Mom, what
are you doing?

30:37.875 --> 30:40.500
(leaves rustling)

30:40.583 --> 30:42.750
(gasps)
I can see it, Els!

30:42.834 --> 30:45.000
It's not far at all!

30:45.083 --> 30:47.166
We can just cross this bit,

30:47.250 --> 30:50.083
and we'll be there in,
like, five minutes.

30:50.166 --> 30:52.000
Ellie:
Maybe we shouldn't.

30:52.083 --> 30:54.875
-Maybe we should just go.
-Oh, come on, Ellie.

30:55.583 --> 30:56.834
We're only five minutes away.

30:56.917 --> 30:58.583
The causeway doesn't close
for half an hour.

30:58.667 --> 31:01.000
There'll be plenty of time
to come back and leave
if we don't like it.

31:01.083 --> 31:05.250
-Talulah: Can we go?
-Come on! This is fun!
(giggling)

31:06.834 --> 31:08.333
-This way!
-Talulah: Okay.

31:08.417 --> 31:11.417
(light guitar playing)

31:11.500 --> 31:13.625
♪ ♪

31:15.834 --> 31:19.000
(waves washing ashore)

31:34.583 --> 31:36.417
Hurry up!

31:37.208 --> 31:39.333
Oh, lazy Ellie!

31:40.208 --> 31:42.250
Please don't take me out!

31:42.333 --> 31:44.458
♪ ♪

31:48.000 --> 31:50.250
Thank you, my darling.

31:50.333 --> 31:53.166
Talulah:
What are we doing for
the rest of the day, Mom?

31:54.041 --> 31:56.542
♪ ♪

31:59.667 --> 32:02.834
(waves washing ashore)

32:06.417 --> 32:09.500
♪ ♪

32:14.667 --> 32:17.709
(indistinct chatter)

32:17.792 --> 32:19.875
♪ ♪

32:39.792 --> 32:42.875
♪ ♪

33:01.375 --> 33:04.542
(plastic crinkling)

33:13.792 --> 33:16.458
(crinkling continues)

33:17.959 --> 33:20.083
Mom, I need a poo.

33:22.667 --> 33:24.667
Mom, I said I needed a poo!

33:24.750 --> 33:26.208
Alright, Lu.

33:26.291 --> 33:28.417
(wind blowing)

33:35.208 --> 33:38.083
Helen:
(sighs) Okay, um...

33:38.166 --> 33:40.417
Okay, let's try over here.

33:46.041 --> 33:47.542
-Wait! Wait!
-(door opens)

33:47.625 --> 33:50.333
(wind whistling)

33:50.417 --> 33:52.583
-Helen: Lu.
-Talulah: Oh, Mom!

33:59.834 --> 34:00.959
(door slams)

34:04.792 --> 34:07.959
(wind continues)

34:15.083 --> 34:17.792
Come on, Lu.
I'll just be a sec, okay?

34:23.500 --> 34:25.166
Helen:
(sighs) Come on.

34:27.792 --> 34:29.709
Lu.

34:29.792 --> 34:32.333
Talulah:
Ugh, the toilet
seat's really cold.

34:32.417 --> 34:34.125
Helen:
Alright, then just hover.

34:36.375 --> 34:38.625
Talulah:
There's no toilet paper.

34:41.709 --> 34:43.458
Helen:
Alright, there you go.

34:45.083 --> 34:46.917
You need to wash your hands
when you're finished.

34:47.000 --> 34:49.041
-Talulah: Okay.
-Helen: I'll just be outside.

34:51.417 --> 34:53.000
(creaking)

35:04.500 --> 35:05.834
(exhales)

35:07.083 --> 35:10.208
(wind blowing)

35:19.291 --> 35:21.667
(creaking)

35:23.083 --> 35:26.125
(tense music playing)

35:26.208 --> 35:28.333
♪ ♪

35:39.208 --> 35:42.375
(plastic crinkling)

36:12.250 --> 36:13.375
(sighs)

36:20.000 --> 36:21.375
Ellie?

36:27.625 --> 36:29.250
Ellie?!

36:30.750 --> 36:33.875
♪ ♪

36:45.458 --> 36:48.625
(tense music continues)

37:12.625 --> 37:14.542
(creaking)

37:14.625 --> 37:17.291
(crinkling)

37:24.208 --> 37:27.208
(wind blowing)

37:27.291 --> 37:30.250
♪ ♪

37:30.333 --> 37:32.834
(creaking)

38:05.083 --> 38:06.291
Mom!

38:06.375 --> 38:08.667
-(plastic opening)
-Ellie!

38:08.750 --> 38:11.875
♪ ♪

38:18.125 --> 38:19.291
Come on.

38:19.375 --> 38:22.208
(ominous music playing)

38:28.125 --> 38:30.250
(wind blowing)

38:47.875 --> 38:50.333
(heavy breathing)

38:50.417 --> 38:51.583
(door slams)

39:05.959 --> 39:08.583
♪ ♪

39:13.709 --> 39:16.625
Preacher:
Bring the love of Christ
into this place.

39:19.083 --> 39:22.250
Surround us in it,
enter this world.

39:23.375 --> 39:25.542
(indistinct whispering)

39:26.667 --> 39:28.709
(heavy breathing)

39:28.792 --> 39:32.041
(speaking Latin)

39:32.125 --> 39:34.041
Bring me your hate
and your soul.

39:34.125 --> 39:36.750
(speaking Latin)

39:37.625 --> 39:39.792
Bring me your love and your--

39:39.875 --> 39:40.959
(knocking)

39:41.792 --> 39:43.917
(knocking)

39:44.709 --> 39:46.083
(knocking)

39:49.917 --> 39:51.250
(door opens)

39:51.333 --> 39:53.000
-Well?
-Jason: Janny's drunk.

39:53.083 --> 39:55.375
-Blind drunk.
-Preacher: Are you serious?

39:55.458 --> 39:57.375
Oh, shit! Oh no!

39:57.458 --> 39:59.750
-Mimir: Calm down!
-Preacher: Calm down?

39:59.834 --> 40:02.333
We can't do this.
We need another plan.

40:02.417 --> 40:05.709
Mimir:
It's fine. This is all
what is meant to be.

40:05.792 --> 40:08.542
This is not fine.
She might not survive.

40:08.625 --> 40:10.417
-We could go to prison--
-(slap)

40:10.500 --> 40:12.417
Mimir:
Coward! Filthy coward!

40:12.500 --> 40:14.458
Whose side are you on?

40:14.542 --> 40:17.458
-You know whose side--
-You chose your side.

40:17.542 --> 40:19.458
You're with us.

40:19.542 --> 40:21.709
Janny obviously chose them.

40:22.375 --> 40:24.500
He'll be dealt with.

40:25.333 --> 40:28.000
Now, you do what
needs to be done.

40:28.083 --> 40:30.875
(woman screaming in distance)

40:33.667 --> 40:34.917
(plastic crinkling)

40:35.000 --> 40:37.417
♪ ♪

40:37.500 --> 40:40.500
-Talulah: Who were those men?
-Helen: We need to go. Come on.

40:42.166 --> 40:43.917
(indistinct chatter)

40:44.000 --> 40:45.750
(wind blowing)

40:45.834 --> 40:47.917
Preacher:
If she wants to, let her out.

40:48.000 --> 40:50.083
Jason:
She's staying in
the fucking car!

40:50.166 --> 40:52.875
(woman screaming)

40:56.041 --> 40:58.583
(dramatic music playing)

40:58.667 --> 41:00.750
(panting)

41:05.875 --> 41:07.417
Run!

41:08.709 --> 41:10.792
(fence rattling)

41:10.875 --> 41:13.166
-Come on! Come on! Come on!
-(grunting)

41:15.000 --> 41:16.500
-(fence rattling)
-Come on!

41:19.583 --> 41:21.709
♪ ♪

41:26.166 --> 41:28.709
-(panting)
-Ellie: Mom, that wasn't a cow!

41:28.792 --> 41:30.709
Helen:
I know, hon! We're leaving!

41:31.542 --> 41:33.333
Talulah:
What's going on? I'm scared.

41:33.417 --> 41:36.208
Helen:
It's okay, Lu! We're leaving
this place, I promise!

41:37.375 --> 41:38.667
-Talulah: Ah!
-(thud)

41:38.750 --> 41:40.291
(panting)

41:40.375 --> 41:44.667
Helen:
Come on, Lu, we just need
to get to the car. Come on.

41:44.750 --> 41:47.667
-Ellie: Is this the way we came?
-Helen: Uh, yeah, I think so.

41:47.750 --> 41:50.333
We've got 11 minutes.
We still got time.

41:50.417 --> 41:51.750
-(squish)
-(grunts)

41:52.250 --> 41:54.083
-Mom!
-Shit.

41:55.125 --> 41:57.333
-Hold onto me. Hold onto me.
-(crying)

41:57.417 --> 41:59.542
-Ellie, gimme your hand.
Gimme your hand.
-My shoe!

41:59.625 --> 42:01.166
Helen:
Forget it.
It's gone now. Come on.

42:01.250 --> 42:04.750
-Come on.
The car's just up here.
-Talulah: Why?!

42:04.834 --> 42:07.917
♪ ♪

42:09.083 --> 42:11.375
It's okay! We're here.

42:11.458 --> 42:12.834
We made it.

42:12.917 --> 42:16.125
-(birds chirping)
-(panting)

42:24.500 --> 42:27.625
(wind blowing)

42:30.625 --> 42:32.166
Did...

42:32.250 --> 42:34.417
Did they steal it?

42:39.500 --> 42:41.000
Gimme your phone.

42:41.083 --> 42:43.166
(panting)

42:44.125 --> 42:45.875
Um...

42:45.959 --> 42:48.125
It's in the glove
compartment.

42:49.291 --> 42:51.542
And yours
was charging.

42:51.625 --> 42:54.500
(wind blowing)

42:57.709 --> 42:58.834
(sighs)

43:01.709 --> 43:05.375
(crows cawing)

43:05.458 --> 43:08.500
-Talulah: Mom, I'm hungry!
-Helen: Yeah, we'll get
something soon, love.

43:08.583 --> 43:11.875
Talulah:
Hey, this is where
that man was crying.

43:14.500 --> 43:17.417
-Mom, what are you doing?
-Helen: Don't worry.
They were leaving.

43:17.500 --> 43:19.208
Talulah:
What are you doing?

43:19.291 --> 43:21.834
-What are you doing, Mom?
-(lock rattling)

43:22.959 --> 43:24.458
Mom!

43:29.875 --> 43:31.792
-Ellie: Mom!
-Talulah: What are you doing?!

43:31.875 --> 43:34.083
Wha-- We're breaking in?!

43:34.166 --> 43:37.041
-Ellie: What if they come back?
-They're not coming back.

43:42.333 --> 43:43.709
(unlocking)

43:44.208 --> 43:45.875
(door creaking)

43:47.542 --> 43:50.000
Talulah:
We're burglaring.
This is burglary!

43:50.083 --> 43:52.250
Helen:
No, it's not burglaring if
we don't take anything.

43:52.333 --> 43:54.500
(light switch clicking)

43:55.333 --> 43:57.417
Fuck. The power's off.

43:57.500 --> 44:00.000
-(door shuts)
-Talulah: Hey, that's
your last swear.

44:04.166 --> 44:06.875
-Ellie: Mom, what are we doing?
-Uh...

44:08.166 --> 44:11.834
Um, we're gonna find
a phone and get help.

44:23.667 --> 44:26.583
(opening drawers)

44:28.375 --> 44:29.917
Ellie:
There's no phone in here.

44:32.250 --> 44:34.458
Talulah:
Maybe they just use mobiles.

44:39.208 --> 44:41.375
Okay, okay, uh...

44:43.125 --> 44:45.917
We're just gonna wait here
until the causeway opens.

44:46.917 --> 44:49.291
Here? It's freezing!

44:52.250 --> 44:54.208
Just stay down here.

44:56.542 --> 44:57.625
(sighs)

45:05.709 --> 45:08.792
♪ ♪

45:12.417 --> 45:13.792
Come here.

45:16.166 --> 45:17.917
Ellie,

45:18.000 --> 45:19.458
why are we here?

45:24.458 --> 45:26.959
Why didn't we leave?

46:02.792 --> 46:04.959
(heavy breathing)

46:06.500 --> 46:10.125
(tense music playing)

46:10.208 --> 46:12.333
♪ ♪

46:17.667 --> 46:19.834
(bumps door, walks away)

46:30.083 --> 46:31.208
Ellie:
Mom?

46:31.959 --> 46:33.041
Hm?

46:34.917 --> 46:37.083
Why did we come here?

46:38.041 --> 46:40.750
I told you, baby.
For your birthday.

46:42.875 --> 46:45.583
I'm not into
archaeology anymore.

46:46.375 --> 46:48.917
I haven't been
since year 7.

46:49.000 --> 46:51.750
Well...
I thought you liked it.

46:51.834 --> 46:54.208
You know I don't.

46:54.291 --> 46:56.375
I don't.

47:02.041 --> 47:03.166
Gran called.

47:03.959 --> 47:06.125
I spoke to her.

47:07.709 --> 47:09.291
(sighs)

47:12.000 --> 47:13.625
Okay, look...

47:14.750 --> 47:17.417
I'm sorry I lied,
alright? But...

47:18.917 --> 47:21.250
You know I don't like
all that religious stuff.

47:21.333 --> 47:24.208
She pumped me full
of it as a kid, and...

47:24.291 --> 47:27.250
-And yeah, I get that
you're interested--
-Stop it, Mom.

47:27.333 --> 47:28.792
-Ellie, I'm just trying--
-Just...

47:29.208 --> 47:31.291
stop, Mom.

47:32.208 --> 47:33.959
Okay? Just stop lying.

47:42.375 --> 47:45.083
Are you scared
I'm a bad person?

47:48.166 --> 47:49.625
What?

47:49.709 --> 47:52.125
It was just--
It was a stupid fight.

47:52.208 --> 47:54.709
And I can go back to school,

47:54.792 --> 47:56.917
you know?
Nothing's gonna happen.

47:57.000 --> 47:58.333
No.

47:59.667 --> 48:01.792
God, no, Els.

48:03.166 --> 48:05.917
I know you're
not a bad person.

48:06.959 --> 48:09.625
Listen to me.
Jesus Christ...

48:10.542 --> 48:12.542
Those girls, alright?

48:12.625 --> 48:15.792
Those stupid
fucking girls...

48:17.250 --> 48:19.166
they've not been through
what you've been through,

48:19.250 --> 48:21.250
what we've been through.

48:23.417 --> 48:26.458
They think I'm... weird.

48:27.291 --> 48:30.083
-Who cares what they think?
-Me.

48:30.166 --> 48:32.208
I care.

48:32.291 --> 48:34.834
Oh, Els, baby.

48:34.917 --> 48:37.125
-Come here.
-(sniffle)

48:37.792 --> 48:40.875
♪ ♪

48:42.000 --> 48:43.250
Look at her.

48:43.333 --> 48:45.166
Her hand's like ice.

48:46.250 --> 48:48.667
Lu? Lu.

48:48.750 --> 48:50.792
Lu, wake up. Wake up! Lulu?

48:50.875 --> 48:52.500
Talulah, wake up.
Wake up, baby.

48:52.583 --> 48:54.583
-Wake up. Sweetheart, wake up.
-(groaning)

48:54.667 --> 48:56.583
We cannot do this.

48:56.667 --> 49:00.000
We're going somewhere warm.
Come on, baby. Walk for Mommy.

49:00.083 --> 49:03.458
♪ ♪

49:23.375 --> 49:24.542
(door opens)

49:25.709 --> 49:28.625
(pub chatter)

49:28.709 --> 49:30.166
(chatter stops)

49:30.250 --> 49:32.625
(door shuts)

49:32.709 --> 49:34.834
-Go over there by the fire.
-Is it okay, Mom?

49:34.917 --> 49:36.792
Yeah, it's fine, hon.
Just go and get warm.

49:36.875 --> 49:38.375
Sorry. We're not open--

49:38.458 --> 49:40.500
-We need a room.
-Oh.

49:40.583 --> 49:42.542
-Well, we don't do
rooms anymore.
-We're not going.

49:43.709 --> 49:46.542
We're not going anywhere.
We're staying right here.

49:46.625 --> 49:47.959
Right, well,
it's not really--

49:48.041 --> 49:50.000
Look, I don't care
what's going on, alright?

49:50.083 --> 49:52.583
Whatever's happening in this
place, I'm not interested

49:52.667 --> 49:55.500
in your arguments,
or your fights,
or the stuff you do.

49:55.583 --> 49:57.000
It doesn't matter to me at all.

49:57.083 --> 49:59.625
But, I have been all over
this fucking island,

49:59.709 --> 50:02.542
and no one will give us a room.

50:02.625 --> 50:04.333
My daughters are freezing.

50:04.417 --> 50:06.000
-(fire crackling)
-Our car was stolen!

50:06.083 --> 50:07.792
Oh, not stolen.
Can't be stolen.

50:07.875 --> 50:10.917
Yeah, it was stolen, which
means we don't even have that.

50:12.000 --> 50:15.000
So we're staying
by that fire all night.

50:15.083 --> 50:16.959
And if you don't want that,
then you're gonna have

50:17.041 --> 50:18.875
to pick us up, throw us out,

50:18.959 --> 50:20.583
and watch as we die
against your front door.

50:20.667 --> 50:22.208
You'll be
wanting dinner.

50:22.291 --> 50:23.667
Mr. Martin:
Love?

50:23.750 --> 50:25.875
Well, it's not the right time.

50:25.959 --> 50:28.583
What, are you gonna
chuck 'em out, idiot?

50:28.667 --> 50:31.417
Think, for fuck's sake.

50:33.250 --> 50:34.417
Your girls?

50:37.125 --> 50:38.583
Yeah, we can
give you a room.

50:38.667 --> 50:41.041
You'll get something
to eat and then sleep.

50:41.125 --> 50:43.208
-You'll be warm.
-Helen: Wait.

50:43.291 --> 50:46.125
(pub murmuring)

50:47.083 --> 50:48.792
Are we safe?

50:49.959 --> 50:52.875
-What?
-I was at that Shoreside place.

50:52.959 --> 50:54.458
There were these medical things,

50:54.542 --> 50:57.041
and we-- we heard screaming.

50:57.125 --> 50:59.709
Everyone here is acting like
something bad's gonna happen.

50:59.792 --> 51:01.750
What do you think's
happening here?

51:01.834 --> 51:04.208
It's just childbirth,
that's all.

51:04.291 --> 51:05.959
What do you mean childbirth?

51:06.041 --> 51:09.166
We've got a woman
in labor on Osea.

51:09.250 --> 51:11.041
She wants to have it here.

51:11.125 --> 51:13.792
We can do that.
I've done it me-self, but...

51:13.875 --> 51:16.250
what you saw was just
medical equipment

51:16.333 --> 51:19.083
in case of an emergency.

51:19.166 --> 51:22.500
But now, our medic's gone
and gotten himself arseholed.

51:22.583 --> 51:25.000
Safest thing would be to
take her to the mainland,

51:25.083 --> 51:26.625
but she's refused that,

51:26.709 --> 51:29.667
and now we're just praying that
her stupidity doesn't kill her.

51:31.041 --> 51:33.417
I saw something
else in that place.

51:33.500 --> 51:36.250
Well, we've had our
customs for years.

51:36.333 --> 51:39.667
They ain't pretty, but I'm not
fucking apologizing for 'em.

51:41.917 --> 51:43.792
Car wasn't stolen, it was towed.

51:43.875 --> 51:45.750
They need clear access.

51:45.834 --> 51:48.667
I'll call Danny and he'll be
back here within the hour.

51:50.792 --> 51:52.333
So we're safe here then?

51:53.333 --> 51:55.041
Burgers alright?

51:56.959 --> 51:58.583
Yeah.

51:59.375 --> 52:00.500
Thank you.

52:00.583 --> 52:03.166
Mr. Martin:
You go get yourself
all warmed up.

52:03.250 --> 52:05.667
(pub chatter continues)

52:05.750 --> 52:08.083
♪ ♪

52:08.166 --> 52:10.875
-(fire crackling)
-Ellie: So good.

52:13.500 --> 52:16.917
Talulah:
So good. It's so
chocolatey and nice.

52:17.000 --> 52:19.041
-(happy gasp)
-Mr. Martin: You warm enough?

52:19.125 --> 52:22.291
-Thank you!
-Mr. Martin: I hope you're
hungry. Here we go.

52:22.375 --> 52:24.041
-Is there anything
else I can get you?
-Ellie: Thank you.

52:24.125 --> 52:26.583
No, that's great.
Thank you. Thanks so much.

52:27.667 --> 52:29.041
(chuckles)

52:30.333 --> 52:33.166
(laughing)

52:34.375 --> 52:36.667
(laughing)

52:36.750 --> 52:38.875
(fire crackling)

52:41.333 --> 52:43.959
(laughter continues)

52:44.542 --> 52:45.917
(indistinct chatter)

52:50.083 --> 52:53.291
-Is it good?
-It's all over your face!

52:53.375 --> 52:55.709
♪ ♪

52:55.792 --> 52:58.583
Yeah, sorry about that.
It's just...

52:58.667 --> 53:01.417
Come on, girls,
get your stuff. Come on.

53:10.291 --> 53:12.417
(door creaks)

53:13.542 --> 53:16.000
-(Helen chuckles)
-Talulah: Oh, this is the best!

53:16.083 --> 53:17.333
Booga booga!

53:17.417 --> 53:19.875
(laughing)

53:19.959 --> 53:21.250
Talulah:
OMG!

53:21.333 --> 53:24.917
-Helen: You happy?
-Lu (sarcastic): No, I'm not!

53:25.000 --> 53:27.667
-Obviously, I'm happy!
-Helen: Oh, good.

53:27.750 --> 53:29.375
Talulah:
Can I sleep in my clothes?

53:29.458 --> 53:31.208
-Helen: No.
-Talulah: Why not?

53:31.291 --> 53:33.917
-Helen: 'Cause you're
just being lazy.
-(indistinct)

53:34.000 --> 53:37.125
♪ ♪

53:51.125 --> 53:53.291
(crunching)

54:15.625 --> 54:17.458
No. No, Lu.

54:17.542 --> 54:19.959
-Brush longer.
-I did. I brushed loads.

54:20.041 --> 54:22.250
-Well, did you floss?
-(sighs)

54:22.333 --> 54:23.583
Floss.

54:23.667 --> 54:25.166
-(scoffs)
-Go on!

54:25.250 --> 54:28.000
(thunder rumbling)

54:32.333 --> 54:35.166
(rain falling)

54:35.250 --> 54:38.333
♪ ♪

54:54.583 --> 54:56.709
(bag zipping)

54:59.250 --> 55:00.667
Talulah:
Happy?

55:01.208 --> 55:02.792
Delighted.

55:02.875 --> 55:05.667
Talulah:
Are we going home
in the morning, Mom?

55:05.750 --> 55:08.417
-Helen: We'll see, baby.
-Talulah: We'll see?

55:09.750 --> 55:12.208
Helen:
Well, it's all
fine now, isn't it?

55:12.291 --> 55:14.291
And it's Els' birthday treat.

55:14.375 --> 55:17.041
(rain continues)

55:17.125 --> 55:19.875
Okay, we'll see in the morning.
I promise, okay?

55:20.750 --> 55:23.417
But now, we...

55:23.500 --> 55:24.875
sleep!

55:27.417 --> 55:29.542
(sighs) Right!

55:29.625 --> 55:32.291
-I'm in the middle!
-(laughter)

55:34.709 --> 55:36.250
(clicking)

55:37.041 --> 55:38.417
(sighs)

55:39.542 --> 55:41.291
(indistinct whispering)

55:41.375 --> 55:43.291
-Helen: Um, excuse me!
-Ellie: Pack it in.

55:43.375 --> 55:45.834
-Helen: No screens in bed! No!
-(groan)

55:45.917 --> 55:48.709
No, Lu! Give it to me.

55:48.792 --> 55:50.542
-Give it.
-(laughs)

55:51.458 --> 55:53.291
Talulah:
Alright, alright, God...

55:53.375 --> 55:56.458
♪ ♪

56:19.458 --> 56:22.583
♪ ♪

56:48.583 --> 56:51.709
♪ ♪

57:41.500 --> 57:42.834
MR. MARTIN:
This is a loving place.

57:42.917 --> 57:45.375
If there's anything
we can do for you, anything...

57:46.542 --> 57:47.542
Well, actually there is.

57:47.792 --> 57:49.125
♪ (INTENSE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

57:49.375 --> 57:52.375
Do you know this man?
He's my husband.

57:52.875 --> 57:54.875
He hasn't been here.
I'm sorry.

57:55.750 --> 57:57.208
HELEN:
Sam is not well.

57:57.917 --> 57:59.291
MRS MARTIN:
Start a new life.

57:59.375 --> 58:00.500
Don't look back.

58:01.709 --> 58:03.041
Do you know
what's going on here?

58:03.667 --> 58:05.166
WOMAN:
Things are out of balance.

58:07.875 --> 58:08.875
And you can heal it.

58:09.417 --> 58:12.375
-HELEN: Sam, have you seen him?
-No stupid questions.

58:12.709 --> 58:14.625
♪ (MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

58:15.625 --> 58:16.625
Why are you lying?

58:16.834 --> 58:18.375
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
